name: Smita’s Lakeview Restaurant & Bar |Best Fish Thali And Authentic Goan Food|

reviews.review_text: Always go and only go for starters dish as they have best cuisine and taste is good. Atmosphere is fantastic with music and lake view point. Main course like thali are okay type. Regarding service they are good for starters like bringing it  quickly but main course they take lot of time. Regarding parking space you forget. Recommended to bring Two wheeler only. It is  also expensive compare to quantity they provide. Overall is Very Good.

Everything was good, at first we thought bit pricey. But when it comes to table, actual quantity was surprisingly good. Quite place with goan music in background. Mr. Bharat served us overall food and he was friendly and a gentleman.

Hi there , I myself n my fiance visited this place when we came across to the video on instagram. I was craving to have the food from a long time while I was in abroad. Sukumar had served us very professionally. Even the food was on time n it was very mouth watering. To everyone reading this if you come to Goa n don’t visit here b eat chonok thali tho kya kaya my friend. Note :my favourite prawns papadom. Thank you

description:
**Smita’s Lakeview Restaurant & Bar: A Taste of Goa's Finest Flavors**

Nestled in the heart of Goa Velha, Smita’s Lakeview Restaurant & Bar has established itself as a gastronomic gem, boasting an impressive rating of 4.2 out of 5 from nearly 4,000 enthusiastic reviewers. Renowned for its delectable fish thali and authentic Goan cuisine, this restaurant continues to attract food lovers with its variety of seafood offerings, including barramundi, mussels, kingfish, and the much-praised rava fry. The consistent crowd and positive feedback are a testament to its inviting atmosphere and culinary delights.

**Ambiance & Design**

Upon entering Smita’s, guests are greeted by a vibrant yet serene ambiance, amplified by the tranquil lake views and the soothing sounds of traditional Goan music that play softly in the background. The dining area boasts a mix of rustic charm and modern comfort, with wooden accents and cozy seating arrangements creating a welcoming environment for both intimate dinners and lively gatherings. Reviewers have praised the “fantastic atmosphere,” spotlighting the outdoor seating that allows for picturesque views, especially during sunset.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

The culinary experience at Smita’s is a celebration of the ocean's bounty, with signature dishes that reflect the rich coastal culture of Goan fare. The fish thali is a must-try, curated to deliver a well-rounded experience of flavors. Many diners have raved about the quality and presentation of the dishes, describing them as “mouth-watering” and “surprisingly plentiful.” Among the highlights are the prawns papadom, lauded by a satisfied patron who emphasized its deliciousness at a recent visit. For seafood enthusiasts, the rava fry stands out, beautifully fried to achieve the perfect crispness. While starters receive consistent acclaim for their speed and taste, some guests noted that the main courses could involve a wait, pointing to the need for patience when indulging in the restaurant's heartier offerings.

**Customer Experience & Service**

Service at Smita’s receives mixed reviews; while starters are delivered with commendable promptness, main courses can take a bit longer to arrive at the table. Patrons have highlighted the friendly nature of the staff—exemplified by Mr. Bharat and Sukumar—who are attentive and eager to enhance the dining experience. While the establishment caters well to those on two-wheelers, parking can be a bit of a challenge, suggesting that guests might want to consider alternate transport options. 

**Popularity & Reviews**

The restaurant's popularity is reflected in its vibrant social media presence, where tantalizing food images and satisfied customer testimonials abound. With several reviews praising both the quality and quantity of the offerings, and a few mentioning the higher price point, the general sentiment leans towards a rewarding experience that justifies the cost. 

**Utilizing Visual Content**

The customer-submitted images provide a captivating glimpse of Smita’s culinary creations and the idyllic setting. The delightful presentation of dishes along with vibrant colors on the plate invite diners to savor the experience, while the lake view captured in some photos portrays an ideal backdrop for memorable meals. 

In conclusion, Smita’s Lakeview Restaurant & Bar is a must-visit culinary destination for anyone seeking authentic Goan food combined with scenic beauty. The flavorsome fish thali and other seafood specialties, coupled with a relaxing dining atmosphere, create a delightful escape that beckons guests back for more. Whether you're in town for a brief visit or a resident seeking to indulge in local culinary delights, Smita’s promises an experience as expansive and inviting as the waters that surround it.
